3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex calculates funding rates hourly using a time-weighted average price (TWAP) mechanism comparing perpetual prices to spot indices. The platform's portfolio margin system allows cross-collateralization across positions, reducing capital requirements for complex strategies. Funding payments are automatically settled every hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.1% per funding period."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM's status as a major Layer 1 token creates consistent trading interest and funding rate volatility on Paradex. The hourly funding frequency provides more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges. Cosmos ecosystem developments and staking yield dynamics often drive directional bias in ATOM perpetuals."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM/USDT on Paradex has shown funding rate volatility correlating with Cosmos network upgrades and IBC protocol developments. Positive funding rates typically emerge during ATOM staking reward announcements or interchain adoption news. The DEX nature means funding rates can diverge significantly from CEX rates during network congestion periods. Monthly average funding has ranged from -0.2% to +0.4% per day during major market movements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex's self-custodial model creates funding rate disparities with centralized exchanges, particularly during high volatility periods. The hourly funding cycle allows for more frequent strategy adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. Portfolio margin enables efficient capital utilization when running multiple ATOM positions across different timeframes. Cross-margining with other cosmos ecosystem tokens like TIA or INJ can enhance overall strategy performance."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"StarkNet network congestion can impact position management during critical funding periods, potentially trapping traders in unfavorable positions. Early-stage platform means lower liquidity compared to established CEXs, affecting large position entries and exits. Smart contract risks inherent in DEX trading require thorough due diligence and position sizing. Gas costs for frequent rebalancing on StarkNet must be factored into arbitrage profitability calculations."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Paradex's hourly funding cycle affect ATOM arbitrage strategies?","answer":"The 1-hour funding frequency provides 8x more arbitrage opportunities compared to standard 8-hour cycles. This allows traders to capture shorter-term funding rate movements and adjust positions more dynamically based on ATOM market conditions."},{"question":"What are the custody advantages of trading ATOM perps on Paradex?","answer":"Paradex's self-custodial model means users retain control of their ATOM and USDT throughout trading. This eliminates counterparty risk from exchange insolvency while still providing institutional-grade perpetual futures functionality."},{"question":"How does portfolio margin work for ATOM positions on Paradex?","answer":"Portfolio margin calculates risk across all positions collectively rather than individually. This means ATOM perpetual positions can be cross-margined with other assets, reducing overall capital requirements and improving funding rate strategy efficiency."},{"question":"What makes ATOM funding rates unique on Paradex compared to CEXs?","answer":"Paradex's DEX structure can create funding rate premiums during network congestion or when institutional demand exceeds CEX availability. The StarkNet infrastructure also means funding calculations may diverge during periods of high on-chain activity."}]}]
